Russian Farmers Plant Spring Crops on 50 Million Hectares

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-06-21T15:50:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/russian-farmers-plant-spring-crops-on-50-million-hectares-1-.html
Russian farmers sowed spring crops
on 50 million hectares (124 million acres) as of today, the
 Agriculture Ministry  said.  Spring grains covered about 30 million hectares, up by 2
million hectares from a year earlier, the ministry said in an e-
mailed statement. The seeding area for sunflowers expanded by
0.8 percent to 7.2 million hectares, while soybean plantings
reached 1.2 million hectares and sugar beets covered about 1.3
million hectares, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter in London at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  